4 SYNOPSIS:
5 The Public Service Commission regulates certain
6 utilities in the state. The commission is comprised of
7 three members who are elected at-large.
8 This bill would increase the number of public
9 service commissioners so that a commissioner is elected
10 from each congressional district, starting in the
11 November 2030 general election and every four years
12 thereafter.
13 This bill would require the newly constituted
14 commission to elect a president from among the
15 commissioners.
16 This bill would require the commission to hold
17 informational public meetings at least annually.
18 This bill would also make nonsubstantive,
19 technical revisions to update the existing code
20 language to current style.
21
22
