92 "§37-1-8
93 (a) The commissioners shall have an office at
94 Montgomery, Alabama, and shall meet there a minimum of once a
95 month, with the public information officer giving notice of
96 the monthly meeting at least one week prior to the meeting,
97 and shall remain in session until all business before them is
98 disposed of; and they shall hold other meetings at such times
99 and places as may be necessary for the proper discharge of
100 their duty, or as the convenience of parties in the judgment
101 of the commission may require. They shall keep a record of all
102 their proceedings, which shall be open at all times to the
103 inspection of the public.
104 (b) The commissioners and staff of the commission shall
105 convene at least one public meeting per calendar year with
106 utility representatives to provide information to the public
107 on cost trends, reliability, resilience, general
108 infrastructure investment plans, competitiveness with peer
109 states, economic development impacts, national trends in
110 energy production, and other regulatory issues the commission
111 deems relevant. The public meetings shall be conducted in a
112 manner that facilitates public participation, addresses
Page 4

